latestPosts.caption:
Work shouldn’t feel like a battle on your not-so-great days ❌

Women go through different phases in their lives—physically and mentally—which take time to adjust to and get comfortable with. It could be your first day of periods, a low morning, a sleepless night with your child, or just a normal, random, confusing day!

We understand the need for space—to take a break, breathe for a moment, and return with renewed energy.

So, we did something… 🤠

We introduced the De-Caff Comfort & NO-JUDGEMENT Room—a space exclusively for our women to rest, recharge, or simply take a break from the many things life throws at them. With recliners, hot bags, chocolates, books, and cozy couches, we aimed to bring the feeling of home into the workplace. A place where they can GO & CHILL, without being judged. 🤓

At Pep Brands, every day is about creating a workplace where women feel valued, cared for, and understood 🫂.

To all the powerful women at Pep—this one’s for you! ❤️

And yes—Happy Women’s Day, every day!

latestPosts.caption:
What do you do when you are under the weather. 
Read some poetry. 
Reading Sahir Ludhianvi after a long time. Not an easy read (or may be I don't have focus needed), but every bit as good. For those who have heard him in movie songs, his writings are in a different league. 
Here's a sher in the context 

ऐ ग़मे दुनिया तुझे क्या इल्म तेरे वास्ते 
किन बहानों से तबियत राह पे लाई गई

Poorly translated as 

dear worldly sorrows, what do you know, 
for your sake
to set it right, what excuses did
my heart make

Got a better translation? Please share

latestPosts.caption:
In this episode, our guest opens up about the raw, unfiltered truth of being an entrepreneur: “For the last 8.5 years, I haven’t had a full night’s sleep. Pain doesn’t kill entrepreneurs; it’s the hope that does. How much to hope? How long to bank on it? There’s no formula.”

Success demands discipline and relentless effort. “Waking up at 5 AM, working 16-hour days, skipping family outings or drinks with friends — it’s the mehnat you put in that makes the difference.” 💪

This conversation is a must-watch for anyone navigating the highs and lows of the entrepreneurial journey. 🌟

🎧 Watch now on YouTube, Spotify, and Apple Podcasts.

In this episode, Vikas Lachhwani, Co-Founder of mCaffeine, shares how a leader’s mindset trickles down through every level of an organization. “Whether it’s a traditional ‘Lala’ mindset or a contemporary ownership-driven culture, it sets the tone for the entire team.” 🌟

Vikas also reflects on the journey of entrepreneurship, emphasizing that there’s no formula for success — but the right resources, especially the right people, can make all the difference. “Sometimes, you need advice, support, or even just a shoulder to rant to. Surround yourself with those who’ll be there when it matters.” 🤝

latestPosts.caption:
“Hustle is extremely necessary and important, but not everyone in the system needs to hustle all the time.”

In this episode, Vikas Lachhwani, Co-Founder of mCaffeine, breaks down the true meaning of hustle and why it’s often misunderstood. Just like in a family where not both parents can be strict all the time, in a system, not everyone can hustle constantly. Hustle isn’t about being constantly busy; it’s about being ready for action and stepping out of your comfort zone when needed. 🏃‍♂️

The key is to understand hustle as being prepared and adaptable, not just endless grinding. It’s about striking the right balance and knowing when to push and when to pause. Let’s redefine hustle the right way! 🚀

🎧 Catch the full conversation—watch the episode on YouTube, Spotify, and Apple Podcasts! 📺
